Semantica
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard


\begin_inset Formula $\semGen ab$
\end_inset

 cioè a è conseguenza semantica di b, se in ogni Frame, Modello e Mondo in cui 
\begin_inset Formula $\vera{\mu}b$
\end_inset

 si ha anche 
\begin_inset Formula $\vera{\mu}a$
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard


\begin_inset Formula $\dia\equiv\sim\boxx{\sim a}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

Vale da sinistra a destra,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

Infatti:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

se 
\begin_inset Formula $\veraw{\mu}{\alpha}{\dia}$
\end_inset

 allora
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard


\begin_inset Formula $\exists\beta:$
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $\alpha R\beta$
\end_inset

 e 
\begin_inset Formula $\veraw{\mu}{\beta}a$
\end_inset

 da cui:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard


\begin_inset Formula $\mu\nvDash_{\beta}\sim a$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

per questo in 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha$
\end_inset

 non vale 
\begin_inset Formula $\boxx{\sim a}$
\end_inset

 (perché non vale 
\begin_inset Formula $\sim a$
\end_inset

 in 
\begin_inset Formula $\beta$
\end_inset

)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

allora in 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha$
\end_inset

 vale 
\begin_inset Formula $\sim\boxx{\sim a}$
\end_inset

 cioè 
\begin_inset Formula $\veraw{\mu}{\alpha}{\sim\boxx{\sim a}}$
\end_inset

 cioè la tesi. 
